sentences: Pietro Tonolo (born 30 May 1959) is an Italian jazz saxophone player and composer.
In 1982, Tonolo joined the Gil Evans Orchestra, playing with notable musicians as Steve Lacy, Lew Soloff and Ray Anderson.
He was a steady member of the Paul Motianâ€™s Electric Bebop Band from 1999 to 2004.
He is currently teaching at the Conservatory of Vicenza and Siena Jazz international masterclasses.
